To uninstall a nvidia from ubunutu 20.14 follw the below commands:

     -   sudo apt-get purge nvidia*
     
     -   sudo apt-get autoremove
     
     -   sudo apt-get autoclean
     
     -   sudo rm -rf /usr/local/cuda*
     
after the commands you will be successfully delete nvidia

to install nvidia run commands in terminal.

before going to install, You will have to download a nvidia drivers which will be in the .run extention from nvidia documentation.

     -    https://docs.nvidia.com/datacenter/tesla/tesla-installation-notes/index.html
   

after downloading reboot the system, once the system is going to start, press "Esc" key. select advanced setting option and root prompt to get the root terminal.

and go to directory where you have installed .run file and run below command.

      -   sudo bash NVIDIA-Linux-x86_64-525.60.11.run

then configure your nvidia and install. after installing reboot the system and open terminal and run "nvidia-smi" to verify the installation.


